  <h2>National Market Size &amp; Growth</h2>

  <p>The U.S. landscaping and lawn care industry is one of the most consistently growing sectors in home services. The numbers vary by what's counted (lawn-only vs. full landscaping services), but every major data source points the same direction: big, fragmented, and still growing.</p>

  <div class="stat-grid">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-val gold">$167B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Industry Size (2024)</div>
      <div class="stat-note">IBISWorld estimate</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-val">6.4%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">3-Year CAGR</div>
      <div class="stat-note">Consistent annual growth</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-val gold">600K+</div>
      <div class="stat-label">US Businesses</div>
      <div class="stat-note">Highly fragmented market</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-val">1.2M+</div>
      <div class="stat-label">US Workers</div>
      <div class="stat-note">3rd largest in its category</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-val gold">8.6%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Top 5 Co. Market Share</div>
      <div class="stat-note">Rest = small operators</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-val">61%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Residential Share</div>
      <div class="stat-note">Homeowners drive demand</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>The most important takeaway for a startup like Rent a Grandson: <strong>the top five national companies combined hold less than 9% of the market.</strong> That means 91%+ belongs to regional and local operators. This is a deeply local business where trust, consistency, and neighborhood reputation win — not brand recognition or national ad budgets.</p>

  <div class="callout">
    <p><strong>Key Trend:</strong> Subscription and recurring maintenance contracts now account for over 75% of new residential bookings for leading providers. Locking in seasonal contracts early is the fastest path to stable, predictable revenue for a new business.</p>
  </div>

  <h3>Why the Industry Keeps Growing</h3>
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>Continued suburban expansion and new home construction driving first-time landscaping needs</li>
    <li>Homeowners treating outdoor spaces as lifestyle investments, not just maintenance</li>
    <li>Aging population increasingly outsourcing physical yard work (prime Rent a Grandson territory)</li>
    <li>Rising home values incentivizing curb appeal investment</li>
    <li>Growing demand for water-efficient landscaping as drought concerns increase</li>
    <li>Even in downturns, homeowners keep paying for small recurring services like mowing</li>
  </ul>
