<!-- SECTION 6: MARKETING -->
<section id="marketing">
<div class="container">
  <div class="section-label">Section 06</div>
  <h2>Marketing Strategy</h2>

  <p>A startup landscaping business in Colorado Springs doesn't need a massive ad budget. It needs a smart local presence, a handful of great reviews, and a brand story that earns word of mouth. Here's how to build the funnel.</p>

  <h3>Phase 1 — Foundation (Before First Client)</h3>
  <div class="strategy-steps">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">1</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Google Business Profile — Do This First</h4>
        <p>Set up and fully complete your Google Business Profile. This is the single highest-ROI free action you can take. The Google 3-pack captures 44–61% of all local search clicks. Add services, photos, hours, and service area. Request reviews after every job with a direct link. <strong>87% of consumers check reviews before contacting a local service.</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">2</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Simple Website with Clear Pricing</h4>
        <p>A fast, mobile-optimized site with your services, approximate pricing, before/after photos, and an easy quote request form. Don't overthink it — one page done well beats five pages done poorly. Over 52% of service searches happen on mobile. Make sure it loads fast and the phone number is clickable.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">3</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Nextdoor + Neighborhood Facebook Groups</h4>
        <p>These are where Colorado Springs homeowners find local services. Create a business page on Nextdoor. Join neighborhood Facebook groups for Briargate, Broadmoor, Banning Lewis Ranch, and other target neighborhoods. Introduce the business genuinely. Post before/after photos when you do good work.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">4</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Direct Mail / Door Hangers — Targeted Neighborhoods</h4>
        <p>Targeted direct mail achieves a 4.4% response rate. Door hangers in specific high-value subdivisions convert at 1–2% with a strong offer. Focus on established residential neighborhoods (older homes, mature trees, existing landscaping). A simple "First mow free when you sign a seasonal contract" offer moves clients quickly.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>Phase 2 — Build Credibility (Months 1–6)</h3>
  <div class="strategy-steps">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">5</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Review Generation System</h4>
        <p>Businesses with 100+ Google reviews and a 4.8+ rating consistently outperform competitors with identical ad budgets and better prices. Text every client after a job: "We really appreciate your business — if you have 60 seconds, a Google review helps a ton." Link directly to your Google review page. Target 15–30 reviews in the first 3 months.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">6</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Instagram / TikTok Before &amp; After Content</h4>
        <p>Visual content converts exceptionally well in Colorado Springs because the mountain backdrop makes even basic landscaping look great. Film short before/after videos — an overgrown lawn becoming clean, a spring cleanup, a mulch refresh. Post consistently. Hashtag #ColoradoSpringsLandscaping, #ColoradoSpringslawncare, #PikesPeakCountry. This builds trust faster than any ad.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">7</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Referral Program</h4>
        <p>Referred customers are 18% less likely to churn and 16–25% more valuable over their lifetime. Offer a $25 account credit for every referral that signs a seasonal contract. Tell every satisfied client: "Our biggest growth is through referrals — if you know someone who needs reliable lawn care, we'd love the introduction."</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>Phase 3 — Scale (Month 6+)</h3>
  <div class="strategy-steps">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">8</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Google Local Services Ads (LSAs)</h4>
        <p>LSAs show above traditional search ads with the "Google Guaranteed" badge and charge per lead rather than per click. Cost per lead runs $29–$101 for home services. Most landscaping advertisers spend $500–$600/month on Google Ads. Once you have 20+ reviews and solid GBP optimization, LSAs will generate consistent inbound leads during peak season (March–June).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">9</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Facebook/Instagram Ads — Seasonal Promotions</h4>
        <p>At $25–$80 per lead with a 6% close rate, paid social works best for higher-ticket seasonal promotions — spring cleanup packages, xeriscape consultations, fall aeration specials. Target homeowners in specific Colorado Springs zip codes (80919, 80920, 80921 for Briargate/Flying Horse; 80906 for Broadmoor). Budget $150–$300/month per campaign.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">10</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Email/SMS to Existing Clients</h4>
        <p>Email marketing delivers $36–$40 for every $1 spent — the highest ROI of any marketing channel. Your existing client list is your most underutilized asset. Spring aeration reminders, fall cleanup specials, winter snow removal enrollment. A simple monthly email keeps you top of mind and converts to additional service bookings at near-zero acquisition cost.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <p><strong>The Brand Advantage:</strong> "Rent a Grandson" is one of the most memorable small business names in the landscaping space. Use it. Tell the story everywhere — the young entrepreneurs who bring the energy, reliability, and care of a grandson helping out. That story earns goodwill, referrals, and media attention that a generic "Green Thumb Lawn Care" never will.</p>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

